# Healthscan-v4 UI conventions

- Visual direction: use the Healthscan-v4 look for all frontend UI updates.
- Keep behavior intact: do not weaken auth, RBAC checks, or route guards while styling.

## Tokens first

- Prefer theme tokens/CSS variables over hardcoded colors:
  - `--surface`, `--surface-2`, `--border`, `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-muted`
  - `--brand-primary`, `--brand-primary-strong`, `--brand-secondary`
  - semantic: `--success`, `--warning`, `--danger`, `--purple`
- Reuse shared utilities from `app/globals.css` (`surface-card`, `pill*`, `tbl-shell`) before creating one-off styles.

## Component styling

- Use shared primitives (`Button`, `Card`, `Input`) instead of ad-hoc page-specific styling.
- Keep cards/tables compact and consistent (rounded-xl/2xl, soft shadow, subtle borders).
- Statuses should use semantic pills (success/warning/danger/info), not plain text color only.

## Layout and shell

- Maintain the dashboard shell hierarchy: strong topbar, fixed-feel sidebar, clean content surfaces.
- Keep spacing system consistent (`gap-2/4/6`, `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`) and avoid random size jumps.
- Mobile drawer/overlay interactions must remain accessible and keyboard-dismissable.

## Scope and safety

- Avoid broad rewrites when small token/primitive updates can achieve the same visual result.
- When updating UI in feature modules, keep existing API contracts and data flow unchanged.
